page.title: 14Millhead,Warton,Nr.Carnforth
page.content:
Millhead, once the site of Warton corn mills, owes its origin as a community to the coming of rail and Iron Works to Carnforth just over the river. The Victorian settlement of terraced cottages remains intact. The main road isolates it from a modern private bungalow estate. People on the older side tend for historical reasons to regard themselves as belonging to Carnforth yet proud of their separate identity. Those on the new side largely identify with Warton.
Social integration is not yet as strong in Millhead as it is in Warton where modern growth started earlier and where ancient ribbon development gave a better base for mixing old and new in depth. Total estimated population is 668.
